mentation showing vapor pressure was provided and an exemption letter from the port surveyor was subsequently issued allowing ventilation in place of prewash after discharge of the biofuel blend."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-08-07T12:45:05.907","modifiedByFull":"Butcher, Carol","remark":"8/4 \u0026 8/5 - Increase in TCE $3K due to addition of demurrage and interim port deviation"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-07-21T12:55:18.43","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"updated time at Thames (1) - no demurrage incurred on 1:1 so time saved is reflected in the interim estimation"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-06-26T19:39:37.263","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"after load completed in St. Rose - SHIFTING TO RESERVE ANCHORAGE MILE 137.36 a/c SOUTHBOUND RIVER CLOSURE AT MILE 101 - 102 FOR REVETMENT WORK"}],"offhireList":[{"id":195216,"dateStartUtc":null,"dateEndUtc":null,"days":null,"displayOrder":0,"offhireReason":null,"remark":null,"offhireBunkerList":[{"id":188697,"gradeName":"HSBF","quantity":null,"price":null,"displayOrder":0}]}],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}